wards|date=December 31, 2017|work=International Business Times}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[2017 KBS Drama Awards|31st]] [[KBS Drama Awards]]\n|Best New Actress\n|rowspan=3|''[[School 2017]]''\n| {{won}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/kbs-drama-awards-2017-kim-young-chul-chun-ho-jin-share-grand-prize-complete-winners-list-755160|title=KBS Drama Awards 2017: Kim Young Chul, Chun Ho Jin share grand prize; complete winners list|date=January 1, 2018|work=International Business Times}}</ref> \n|-\n|Netizen Award\n|{{nom}}\n| \n|-\n| 2018\n| [[54th Baeksang Arts Awards]]\n|Best New Actress (TV)\n|{{nom}}\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.jtbc.joins.com/html/136/NB11615136.html|title=\uc81c54\ud68c \ubc31\uc0c1\uc608\uc220\ub300\uc0c1, TV\u00b7\uc601\ud654 \uac01 \ubd80\ubb38\ubcc4 \uc218\uc0c1 \ud6c4\ubcf4\uc790 \uacf5\uac1c|date=April 6, 2018|website=JTBC|language=ko}}</ref> \n|- \n|}\n\n=== Music programs ===\n\n====[[Show Champion]]====\n{{South Korean music program awards table}}\n|-\n| 2016\n| November 30<ref name=\"showchampion1\"/>\n| \"Flower Way\"\n{{end}}\n\n====[[The Show (South Korean TV series)|The Show]]====\n{{South Korean music program awards table}}\n|-\n| 2020\n| March 24\n| \"Plant\"\n{{end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commonscat|Kim Se-jeong}}\n* {{Hancinema person |Kim_Sejeong}}\n{{Gugudan}} \n{{I.O.I}}\n{{Produce 101}}\n{{K-pop Star}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kim, Sejeong}}\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:People from Anyang, Gyeonggi]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Jellyfish Entertainment artists]]\n[[Category:South Korean female idols]]\n[[Category:South Korean female pop singers]]\n[[Category:South Korean television actresses]]\n[[Category:K-pop Star participants]]\n[[Category:Produce 101 contestants]]\n[[Category:Gugudan]]\n[[Category:I.O.I members]]\n[[Category:King of Mask Singer contestants]]\n[[Category:21st-century women singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century South Korean singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century South Korean actresses]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-sock|small=yes}}\n{{short description|South Korean singer}}\n{{Korean name|Kim}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name            = Kim Se-jeong\n| image           = 171231 \uad6c\uad6c\ub2e8 \uc138\uc815 KBS \uc5f0\uae30\ub300\uc0c1 \ub808\ub4dc\uce74\ud3ab 4 (cropped).jpg\n| caption         = Kim Se-jeong in December 2017\n| image_size      = 230px\n| native_name     = \uae40\uc138\uc815\n| birth_name      = Kim Se-jeong\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age |1996|8|28}}\n| birth_place     = [[Gimje]], [[North Jeolla Province|North Jeolla]], South Korea\n| education       = [[Hanyang Women's University]]\n| occupation      = {{hlist|Singer|actress}}\n| module          = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background      = solo_singer\n| genre           = [[K-pop]]\n| instrument      = Vocals\n| years_active    = 2016\u2013present\n| label           = {{hlist|[[Jellyfish Entertainment]]|[[YMC Entertainment]]}}\n| associated_acts = {{hlist|[[I.O.I]]|[[Gugudan]]|[[Gugudan SeMiNa]]}}\n| module          = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes\n| title           = [[Korean name]]\n| hangul          = {{linktext|\uae40|\uc138|\uc815}}\n| hanja           = {{linktext|\u91d1|\u4e16|\u6b63}}\n| rr              = Gim Se-jeong\n| mr              = Kim Sech\u014fng\n}}}}}}\n\n'''Kim Se-jeong''' (born August 28, 1996), better known by the mononym '''Sejeong''', is a South Korean singer and actress signed under [[Jellyfish Entertainment]]. She is best known as the runner-up contestant in ''[[Produce 101]]'', a former member of the girl group [[I.O.I]], and as a member of [[Gugudan]] and its subgroup Gugudan Semina. She was a co-host of the variety show ''[[Talents for Sale]]'' in 2016 and played the leading role in the teen drama, ''[[School 2017]]''.\n\n== Early life and education ==\nKim Se-jeong was born in [[Gimje]], [[North Jeolla Province]], but moved to [[Anyang, Gyeonggi]] where she stayed with her mother and older brother at her aunt's house. Her parents split when she was a child, leaving her mother to single-handedly raise her and her brother, and she has previously stated that she did not contact her father until her third year of middle school.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20160518n04251?mid=n1008|title='\ub2d8\uacfc\ud568\uaed82' \uae40\uc138\uc815 \"\uc544\ubc84\uc9c0 \uc9113\ub54c 10\ub144 \ub9cc\uc5d0 \ubd24\ub2e4\" \uac00\uc815\uc0ac \uacf5\uac1c|language=Korean|date=May 18, 2016|publisher=Nate|accessdate=June 18, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dispatch.co.kr/523112|title=\uae40\uc138\uc815 \"10\ub144 \ub9cc\uc5d0 \ub9cc\ub09c \uc544\ube60, \uccab\uc778\uc0ac\ub294 \ubbf8\uc548\"(\uc601\uc0c1)|date=May 24, 2016|access-date=June 23, 2016|work=Dispatch|language=ko}}</ref> Kim is currently studying practical music in [[Hanyang Women's University]].\n\n== Career ==\nIn 2012, Kim participated in the second season of competition television show ''[[K-pop Star 2]]'' at the age of 16.<ref name=\"kpopstar2\">{{cite news|url=http://stoo.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2016021308402015140|title=\ud504\ub85c\ub4c0\uc2a4101 \uc21c\uc7041\uc704 \uae40\uc138\uc815, 3\ub144\uc804 'K\ud31d\uc2a4\ud0c02' \uc2dc\uc808 \uc5b4\ub560\ub098|work=Asiae|accessdate=June 23, 2016|date=February 13, 2016|language=ko}}</ref><ref name=\"kpopstar3\">{{cite news|url=http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2016/02/20/2016022001708.html|title=\ud504\ub85c\ub4c0\uc2a4101 \uc21c\uc7041\uc704 \uae40\uc138\uc815, 3\ub144\uc804 'K\ud31d\uc2a4\ud0c02' \uc2dc\uc808 \uc5b4\ub560\ub098|work=The Chosun Ilbo|language=ko|date=February 20, 2016|accessdate=February 28, 2017}}</ref> She did not make it through the second round ranking audition, but [[Yang Hyun-suk]] brought her back as a wildcard for the casting round, where she performed a duet of [[Taeyang]]'s \"I Need A Girl\" with fellow contestant Jo Yoo-min.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2013/01/06/2013010600996.html|title='K\ud31d\uc2a4\ud0c02' \uc870\uc724\ubbfc\u00b7\uae40\uc138\uc815, YG \ub3d9\ubc18 \uce90\uc2a4\ud305..'\uae5c\uc9dd'|work=The Chosun Ilbo|date=January 6, 2013|access-date=June 26, 2016|language=ko}}</ref> Yang cast the both of them, grouping Kim with contestants Nicole Curry and Lee Soo-kyung for the final casting round. However, at the end of the round, she was eliminated from the competition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.tf.co.kr/read/entertain/1131433.htm|title='\ucf00\uc774\ud31d \uc2a4\ud0c02' YG\ud45c \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9, \ud639\ud3c9 \uc18d \ub2c8\ucf5c \ucee4\ub9ac\ub9cc YG\ud589|last=|work=The Fact|date=20 January 2013|language=ko-KR|access-date=June 23, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===''Produce 101'' and I.O.I===\n\nIn January 2016, she represented [[Jellyfish Entertainment]] together with fellow trainees Kim Na-young and Kang Mi-na on the reality survival show ''[[Produce 101]]'' for the chance to debut in a Mnet girl group.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://pann.nate.com/talk/330211039|title=\uc824\ub9ac\ud53c\uc26c\uac00 \uc560\ub4e4\uc798\ubf51\uc74c(\ud504\ub85c\ub4c0\uc2a4101)|date=February 13, 2016|work=Nate|language=Korean|accessdate=December 1, 2016}}</ref> All three were assigned to \"Group A\" in the first episode of the program, and she achieved the first-place ranking on several episodes,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2016/03/12/2016031200071.html|title='\ud504\ub85c\ub4c0\uc2a4101' \uae40\uc138\uc815 1\uc704 \uc9c0\ucf30\ub2e4\u20262\uc704 \ucd5c\uc720\uc815\u00b73\uc704 \uac15\ubbf8\ub098|access-date=June 26, 2016|website=The Chosun Ilbo}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.donga.com/BestClick/3/all/20160220/76553546/1|title=\ud504\ub85c\ub4c0\uc2a4 101 \uae40\uc138\uc815 1\uc704, \ub208\ubb3c \uc18c\uac10\u2026\ucd5c\uace0 \uc2dc\uccad\ub960 \uacbd\uc2e0|website=The Donga Ilbo|date=20 February 2016|access-date=June 23, 2016}}</ref> earning the nickname \"God Sejeong\". The program came to an end on April 1, 2016, and the final line-up of [[I.O.I]], made up of the top 11 poll-winners, was announced. Kim finished second overall, with 525,352 votes, becoming an official member of the girl group.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/culture/2016/04/201_201874.html|title=101 girls down to 'I.O.I'|work=The Korea Times|date=April 4, 2016}}</ref> I.O.I promoted as a whole for events and advertising gigs.<ref>{{Cite web |url= http://news.nate.com/view/20160731n06025?mid=n1008 |title= [\ub2e8\ub3c5] \"I.O.I \uc644\uc804\uccb4 8\uc6d4\uc5d0\ub3c4 \ucb49\"\u2026\uc774\ubca4\ud2b8+CF\ub85c \ubb49\uce5c\ub2e4 |agency= \ub124\uc774\ud2b8\ub274\uc2a4 |language= ko-KR |access-date= August 9, 2016 |website= Nate.com }}</ref>\n\n===Gugudan and solo career===\nPlans for Kim to host a new KBS show ''[[Talents for Sale]]'' alongside [[Kim Jong-kook (singer)|Kim Jong-kook]], [[Lee Seo-jin]] and [[Noh Hong-chul]] were announced in April 2016.<ref name=talents>{{Cite news |url= http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/923475 |title= \uae40\uc138\uc815, '\uc5b4\uc11c\uc635\uc1fc' \uace0\uc815 \ucd9c\uc5f0\u2026\uc9c0\uc0c1\ud30c \uc608\ub2a5 \uc2e0\uace0\uc2dd\ud150\uc544\uc2dc\uc544 {{!}} \ud150\uc544\uc2dc\uc544 |date= April 21, 2016 |accessdate= June 23, 2016 |work=TenAsia |language= ko}}</ref> She displayed a variety of talents on the show and earned the nickname 'Variety Cheat Key'.<ref>{{Cite news|language=ko|url=http://www.asiatoday.co.kr/view.php?key=20160618000946048|title='\uc5b4\uc11c\uc635\uc1fc' \uae40\uc138\uc815, \uc5f4\uc77c\ud558\ub294 '\uc7ac\ub2a5 \uce58\ud2b8\ud0a4!'\u2026\ub7a9\ubd80\ud130 \ud314\uc528\ub984\uae4c\uc9c0 \ubabb\ud558\ub294 \uac8c \uc5c6\ub294 \uc694\uc815!|accessdate=August 9, 2016|work=Asia Today}}</ref> On June 10, 2016, YMC Entertainment revealed that Kim would not be taking part in I.O.I's unit promotions but would instead return to her agency to debut and promote with its upcoming girl group.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=057&aid=0000973823|title=I.O.I, \uc720\ub2db \uba64\ubc84 \ud655\uc815\u2026'\uc804\uc18c\ubbf8-\uc8fc\uacb0\uacbd-\ucd5c\uc720\uc815 \ub4f1 7\uc778'(\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5)|language=ko|date=June 10, 2016|work=Star MBN|accessdate=December 1, 2016}}</ref> On June 28, 2016, Kim officially debuted as a member of South Korean girl group [[Gugudan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201606071441159116280_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|title=Kim Se-jeong, Kang Mi-na join Jellyfish's first girl group|date=June 6, 2016|work=Kpop Herald}}</ref> On November 23, 2016, Kim participated in Jellyfish Entertainment\u2019s music channel project ''[[Jelly Box]]'' and released the single \"[[Flower Way]]\" ({{Korean|\uaf43\uae38||Kkotgil}}), produced by [[Zico (rapper)|Zico]], along with a music video.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201611161645299549870_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|title=I.O.I's Kim Se-jeong to finish track with Zico|date=November 16, 2016|work=Kpop Herald}}</ref> The single topped seven major charts upon its release,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201611231432245865629_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|title='Flower Road' by I.O.I's Kim Se-jeong tops local chart|date=November 23, 2016|work=Kpop Herald}}</ref> and Kim received her first music program trophy as a solo artist with \"Flower Way\" on the November 30th episode of ''[[Show Champion]]''.<ref name=\"showchampion1\">{{cite web|title=Gugudan\u2032s Kim Se Jeong Wins First Music Program as Solo Artist|url=http://mwave.interest.me/en/kpop-news/article/110537/gugudans-kim-se-jeong-wins-first-music-program-as-solo-artist-all-kpop-news|work=enewsWorld|accessdate=December 1, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOn January 12, 2017, Kim released the song \"If Only\" for the OST of the Korean drama ''[[The Legend of the Blue Sea]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201701050956410410|work=Newsen|date=January 5, 2017|accessdate=February 28, 2017|title=\uad6c\uad6c\ub2e8 \uae40\uc138\uc815 \uce21 \"'\ud478\ub978\ubc14\ub2e4' OST '\ub9cc\uc5d0\ud558\ub098' \ucc38\uc5ec \ud655\uc815\"(\uacf5\uc2dd)|language=ko}}</ref> That month, she became a permanent MC for [[OnStyle]]'s ''Get It Beauty''.<ref name=\"hostGIB\">{{cite news|title=\uad6c\uad6c\ub2e8 \uc138\uc815, '\uac9f\uc787\ubdf0\ud2f0' \uace0\uc815 MC\ub85c \ubc1c\ud0c1|url=http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=312&aid=0000234157|website=10Asia|accessdate=January 21, 2017|language=ko|date=January 20, 2017}}</ref> In July 2017, she took on her first major acting role as the lead, Ra Eun-ho, in [[KBS2]]'s teen drama ''[[School 2017]]''.<ref name=school2017>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201706061706499215889_2|title=Kim Se-jung confirms role in 'School 2017'|date=June 6, 2017|work=Kpop Herald}}</ref>\nLater that year, she sang \"Star Blossom\" for [[SM Station]] with [[NCT (band)|NCT]]'s Doyoung.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/7998558/nct-doyoung-gugudan-kim-sejeong-star-blossom-duet|title=NCT's Doyoung and gugudan's Kim Sejeong Duet on Romantic 'Star Blossom'|work=Billboard|date=October 13, 2017|accessdate=October 17, 2017}}</ref> In September 2017, It was confirmed that Kim will be a fixed cast member in [[Netflix]]'s variety show ''[[Busted!]]''.<ref name=busted>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=3046497|title=Netflix announces star-studded reality show|date=April 5, 2018|website=Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2018, a Gugudan subgroup named Gugudan Semina was formed with Sejeong and members Mina and Nayoung. They debuted on July 10, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201807041317541594623_2|title=Gugudan's 'Semina' holds dual meaning|date=July 4, 2018|website=Kpop Herald}}</ref> In September 2018, Sejeong released the song \"Lover\" for the OST of the Korean drama ''[[Mr. Sunshine (2018 TV series)|Mr. Sunshine]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201809131543202564701_2|title=Sejeong to release track for 'Mr. Sunshine'|date=September 13, 2018|website=Kpop Herald}}</ref> After a year of hiatus as a singer, on December 2, 2019, Kim released the single \"Tunnel\" with Dingo Music, followed by her first EP \"Plant\" ({{Korean|\ud654\ubd84||Hwabun}}), with its lead single of the same name, released on March 17, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kim Se-jeong is ready to make a solo statement : Gugudan member brings her personality to TV and new EP|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3075077|work=Korea JoongAng Daily|accessdate=March 29, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{See also|I.O.I discography|Gugudan discography|Gugudan SeMiNa#Discography}}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\"|Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" |Year\n! scope=\"col\" |Peak chart position\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" |Sales\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\"|Album\n|-\n! style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%\" |[[Gaon Music Chart|KOR<br>Gaon]]<br><ref name=\"gaon-digital\">{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL |title=Gaon Digital Chart |work=Gaon Chart |publisher=Korea Music Content Industry Association |accessdate=February 9, 2017 |language=Korean |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150204071600/http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL |archivedate=February 4, 2015 |df= }}\n*{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?serviceGbn=ALL&termGbn=week&hitYear=2016&targetTime=48&nationGbn=T |title=Flower Way }}\n*{{cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=12&hitYear=2020&termGbn=week |title