{"title_page": "Raphel Cherry", "text_new": "{{short description|American football defensive back}}\n{{Infobox gridiron football person\n| name = \n| image = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1961|12|19}}\n| birth_place = [[Little Rock, Arkansas]]\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| team = \n| number = 37, 45\n| status = \n| position1 = [[Defensive back]]\n| height_ft = \n| height_in = \n| weight_lb = \n| college = [[University of Hawaii|Hawaii]]\n| NFLDraftedYear = 1985\n| NFLDraftedRound = 5\n| NFLDraftedPick = 122\n| NFLDraftedTeam = \n| playing_years1 = 1985\n| playing_team1 = [[Washington Redskins]]\n| playing_years2 = 1987\u20131988\n| playing_team2 = [[Detroit Lions]]\n| career_highlights = \n| NFL = CHE385619\n| DatabaseFootball = CHERRRAP01\n}}\n'''Raphel Jerome Cherry''' (born December 19, 1961 in [[Little Rock, Arkansas|Little Rock]], [[Arkansas]]) is a former [[American football]] [[defensive back]] in the [[National Football League]] for the [[Washington Redskins]] and the [[Detroit Lions]].  He played [[college football]] at the [[University of Hawaii]].\n\nIn 1999, Cherry was convicted of first degree murder in the death of his wife.  He was initially sentenced to [[life imprisonment]],<ref>[http://starbulletin.com/1999/08/25/sports/story1.html ''Raphel Cherry convicted of murdering wife'']</ref> but upon appeal of his conviction, his sentenced was reduced to 30 years. Cherry's estimated release date is January 9, 2029.<ref>[http://caselaw.lp.findlaw.com/scripts/getcase.pl?court=ar&vol=supreme/2002a/20020214/cr01-858&invol=2 ''Raphel CHERRY v. STATE of Arkansas'']</ref>\n\n{{Infobox criminal\n| name   = Raphel Cherry\n| image_name     = \n| image_size     = \n| image_alt      =\n| image_caption  = \n| nationality    =\n| birth_name     = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|mf=y|1961|12|19}}\n| birth_place = Little Rock, Arkansas\n| death_date  = \n| death_place = \n| cause          = \n| alias          = \n| motive    