{"title_page": "Dundreich", "text_new": "{{Infobox mountain\n| name = Dundreich\n| photo = Heather burning, Portmore - geograph.org.uk - 1335961.jpg\n| photo_caption = \n| elevation_m = 623\n| elevation_ref = <ref name=\"hill\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hill-bagging.co.uk/mountaindetails.php?qu=S&rf=1805|title=Dundreich|website=www.hill-bagging.co.uk}}</ref>\n| prominence_m = 67\n| prominence_ref = <ref name=\"hill\" />\n| listing = [[List of Donald mountains in Scotland|Donald]]\n| translation =\n| language =\n| pronunciation =\n| location = [[Scottish Borders]], [[Scotland]]\n| range = [[Moorfoot Hills]], [[Southern Uplands]]\n| coordinates = \n| grid_ref_UK = NT 27465 49086\n| topo = [[Ordnance Survey|OS]] ''Landranger'' 73\n| easiest_route = \n}}\n\n'''Dundreich''' is a hill in the [[Moorfoot Hills]] range, part of the [[Southern Uplands]] of Scotland. Its close proximity to [[Edinburgh]] allows for an almost unimpeded view towards the city, as well as into the [[Pentland Hills]] and surrounding counties. Tied with [[Whitehope Heights]] as the lowest Moorfoot [[Donald (hill)|Donald]], it is most frequently climbed from the Gladhouse Reservoir to the north, often as part of a round of the neighbouring hills.<ref name=\"hill\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Uncategorized|date=April 2020}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox mountain\n| name = Dundreich\n| photo = Heather burning, Portmore - geograph.org.uk - 1335961.jpg\n| photo_caption = \n| elevation_m = 623\n| elevation_ref = <ref name=\"hill\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hill-bagging.co.uk/mountaindetails.php?qu=S&rf=1805|title=Dundreich|website=www.hill-bagging.co.uk}}</ref>\n| prominence_m = 67\n| prominence_ref = <ref name=\"hill\" />\n| listing = [[List of Donald mountains in Scotland|Donald]]\n| translation =\n| language =\n| pronunciation =\n| location = [[Scottish Borders]], [[Scotland]]\n| range = [[Moorfoot Hills]], [[Southern Uplands]]\n| coordinates = \n| grid_ref_UK = NT 27465 49086\n| topo = [[Ordnance Survey|OS]] ''Landranger'' 73\n| easiest_route = \n}}\n\n'''Dundreich''' is a hill in the [[Moorfoot Hills]] range, part of the [[Southern Uplands]] of Scotland. Its close proximity to [[Edinburgh]] allows for an almost unimpeded view towards the city, as well as into the [[Pentland Hills]] and surrounding counties. Tied with [[Whitehope Heights]] as the lowest Moorfoot [[Donald (hill)|Donald]], it is most frequently climbed from the Gladhouse Reservoir to the north, often as part of a round of the neighbouring hills. <ref name=\"hill\" />\n\n===References===\n{{reflist}}\n", "name_user": "CAPTAIN RAJU", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up, addeduncategorisedtag", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dundreich"}
